items.title: i586 & armv7l errors
items.body:
I am doing builds at https://build.opensuse.org/package/show/home:jayvdb:py-new/python-typepy , and seeing similar errors on only i586 & armv7l 

i586:
```
[   65s] =================================== FAILURES ===================================
[   65s] ____________ Test_DateTime_is_type.test_normal[2147483647-0-False] _____________
[   65s] 
[   65s] self = <test_checker_datetime.Test_DateTime_is_type object at 0xb684c50c>
[   65s] value = 2147483647, strict_level = 0, expected = False
[   65s] 
[   65s]     @pytest.mark.parametrize(
[   65s]         ["value", "strict_level", "expected"],
[   65s]         list(
[   65s]             itertools.product(
[   65s]                 [datetime(2017, 3, 22, 10, 0, tzinfo=tzoffset(None, 32400)), date(2017, 3, 22)],
[   65s]                 [StrictLevel.MIN, StrictLevel.MIN + 1, StrictLevel.MAX],
[   65s]                 [True],
[   65s]             )
[   65s]         )
[   65s]         + list(
[   65s]             itertools.product(
[   65s]                 [None, "invalid time string", six.MAXSIZE, "100-0004"],
[   65s]                 [StrictLevel.MIN, StrictLevel.MIN + 1, StrictLevel.MAX],
[   65s]                 [False],
[   65s]             )
[   65s]         )
[   65s]         + list(itertools.product(["2017-03-22T10:00:00+0900"], [StrictLevel.MIN], [True]))
[   65s]         + list(itertools.product(["2017-03-22T10:00:00+0900"], [StrictLevel.MAX], [False])),
[   65s]     )
[   65s]     def test_normal(self, value, strict_level, expected):
[   65s]         type_object = class_under_test(value, strict_level)
[   65s]     
[   65s] >       assert type_object.is_type() == expected
[   65s] E       assert True == False
[   65s] E        +  where True = <bound method DateTime.is_type of value=2147483647, typename=DATETIME, strict_level=0, is_type=True, try_convert=2038-01-19 03:14:07>()
[   65s] E        +    where <bound method DateTime.is_type of value=2147483647, typename=DATETIME, strict_level=0, is_type=True, try_convert=2038-01-19 03:14:07> = value=2147483647, typename=DATETIME, strict_level=0, is_type=True, try_convert=2038-01-19 03:14:07.is_type
[   65s] 
[   65s] test/checker/test_checker_datetime.py:50: AssertionError
```
